Module com.example.softmeth_project3
Package com.example.softmeth_project3

Class GymManagerController

java.lang.Object
com.example.softmeth_project3.GymManagerController
public class GymManagerController extends Object
Reads from GUI input and tests all classes and actions. Allows adding, removing, dropping classes, and checking into classes. Allows printing schedules and members based on sort criteria.
Author:
William Chen, Kalrav Pandit

    • runAddCommand

      private String runAddCommand(String[] split, MemberDatabase mb)
      Adds a member to the member database given a string from standard input. Rejects if: - date is not valid, - date of birth is today or in the future, - member is invalid input: '<' 18 years of age, - member is already in the database, - or location does not exist.
      Parameters:
      split - The split input line read from standard input.
      Returns:
      result The result of this action

    • checkForClass

      private int checkForClass(String name, String loc, String instructor, FitnessClass[] classSessions)
      Checks if a class session exists in the array of class sessions. Determines if instructor exists, location is valid, and if a class by an instructor exists.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the class to search for.
      loc - the location of the class to search for.
      instructor - the instructor of the class to search for.
      classSessions - the array of class sessions to search for the given class.
      Returns:
      the index of the class session in the array, or -1 if not found.

    • dropClass

      private String dropClass(String[] split, MemberDatabase mb, FitnessClass[] classSessions)
      Drops a member from a class, given information of member and class from standard input. Rejects if member did not check in, member is not in the database, or birth date is invalid.
      Parameters:
      split - The split input line read from standard input.
      mb - The member database to reference and find a member
      classSessions - the class session database
      Returns:
      result The result of this action

    • dropGuest

      private String dropGuest(String[] split, MemberDatabase mb, FitnessClass[] classSessions)
      Drops guest from a fitness class, given the member that the guest was under. Rejects if birthdate is invalid, member is not in database, member did not check in a guest, or member cannot have guests.
      Parameters:
      split - The split input line read from standard input.
      mb - The member database to reference and find a member
      classSessions - the class session database
      Returns:
      result The result of this action

    • checkIntoClass

      private String checkIntoClass(String[] split, MemberDatabase mb, ClassSchedule scheduleClasses)
      Checks a member into a fitness class, given information of the member and class based on standard input. Rejects if: - date is not valid, - member is not in database, - class does not exist, - membership is expired, - member checking into the wrong location, - class conflict exists, - or already checked in.
      Parameters:
      split - The split input line of information read from standard input.
      mb - The member database to reference and find a member
      scheduleClasses - the class session schedule
      Returns:
      result The result of this action
